sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TtrpC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: TtrpC is a terminator of tryptophan synthase of Aspergillus nidulans.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the plasmid p71 from the Center for Microbial Biotechnology at the Technical University of Denmark plasmid collection.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Compatible with the Plug'n'Play assembly standard

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1-NLS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From p71-mRFP1 of the Center for Microbial Biotechnology plasmid collection at the Technical University of Denmark. The NLS sequence was synthesized.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was designed for the Plug'n'Play with DNA assembly standard (RFC 80), therefore this part contains tails at the 5' and 3' ends as shown on the figure below. Please notice that mRFP1-NLS is not the same as BBa_K678030, BBa_K678031, or BBa_K678032.
